Fresh Pi session: SIMULATED EXECUTION (read-only).

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design doc: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Issues file: {{run.issues-file}}
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}

Goal:
Simulate the implementation described by the design, or address all
outstanding issues from prior review/manual-testing attempts — *without
mutating the repository*. Do not run the real implementation; produce a
precise description of what would be changed instead.

Rules (strict — this workflow forbids source mutation):
- Do not edit source files. You do not have the `edit` tool, and you must
  not use `bash` (redirects, `tee`, `sed -i`, `patch`, etc.) to write to
  any tracked or untracked file under the worktree.
- Do not run `git commit`, `git add`, or any mutation command.
- Do not run package install, build, codegen, migration, or any step that
  writes to the worktree (e.g. `npm install`, `npm run build`, codegen
  scripts, database migrations).
- `write` may only target files under the `{{run.dir}}/execution/`
  artifact directory. Never `write` to source paths.
- Leave the worktree working tree clean. The review node may run
  `git status --porcelain` and fail if the tree is dirty.
- Keep the simulated change focused on the prompt and design.

What to produce instead of real edits:
- Describe the precise edits you *would* make, file by file, with intended
  diffs in fenced code blocks (prose diffs are fine). For each file,
  explain the location, the old/new text, and the rationale.
- Describe the validation commands you *would* run and the expected
  outcome; do not run commands that mutate the worktree. Read-only checks
  (`git diff`, `grep`, `ls`, reading files) are fine.
- If prior issues exist, address each one in the simulated plan and note
  how the would-be edits resolve it.

Write:
- Summary: {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/execution/status-{{run.round}}.json
- If failing: {{run.dir}}/execution/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status JSON examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"simulated implementation described; no source mutation","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"blocked: design is internally contradictory","issues_file":"execution/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}

The summary must explicitly state that no source files were modified and
that the worktree working tree was left clean.